amass enum -d domain.com -o domain.sub

Resolve domains with massdns

git clone https://github.com/blechschmidt/massdns.git
cd massdns
make

/bin/massdns -r lists/resolvers.txt -t A -o S -w domain.sub

Cut domains column with below command

cut -d " " -f1 domains.sub | sed 's/.$//' | sort -u > domains-final.sub

One Liner for all

subfinder -d apple.com | tee subdomains.txt && assetfinder apple.com | tee -a subdomains.txt && cat subdomains.txt | sort -u | massdns -r $resolver/resolvers.txt -t A -o S -w resolved-domains.txt && cut -d " " -f1 resolved-domains.txt | sed 's/.$//' | tee final-domains.txt && cat final-domains.txt | naabu -json | tee ports.json && cat final-domains.txt | httpx -title | tee live-sites.txt && cat live-sites.txt | nuclei -t $nuct/vulnerabilities/ -t $nuct/cves/ -t $nuct/default-logins/ -t $nuct/misconfiguration/ -t $nuct/miscellaneous/ -t $nuct/fuzzing/ -o nuclei-results.txt
